### Vinyl Casement Windows: Engineering Performance Specifications

#### Compression Seal & Air Leakage
- Multi-point locking mechanism pulls sash against frame gasket.
- Typical air leakage: ≤0.03 cfm/ft² (ASTM E283).
- Beats AAMA Class 630 RC requirements.

#### Thermal Performance (Frame + Glazing)
- Multi-chambered uPVC profiles provide natural thermal break.
- U-Factor: 0.22 to 0.18 with triple glazing (Low-E, Argon).
- SHGC: 0.21 – 0.60 (customizable via coatings).

#### Structural & Security
- Design Pressure (DP) Rating: DP50+ per AAMA/WDMA/CSA 101/I.S.2/A440.
- Multi-point lock engagement (2–4 points) prevents forced entry.
- Water Resistance: 8.0 – 12.0 psf.

#### Acoustic Performance
- Unobstructed compression seal outperforms sliding interfaces.
- STC 35–38 (standard glass); STC 40+ (asymmetric laminated: 3/16″ – 1/2″ – 5/32″).

#### Material Maintenance
- Co-extruded uPVC — no painting, no warping, no rot.
- Designed for 30+ year lifecycle.

